name: NPR
text:
An NPR report revealed the Trump administration awarded over $6 billion in vaccine contracts through a third party. Government contracts executed this way aren't required to include taxpayer protections. 

Now, it faces calls to disclose those contracts. https://t.co/FHEOk5iPSE

name: NPR
text: As politicians prepare for the possibility of a contested election, Gen. Mark Milley, the chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, says the military "will obey the lawful orders of civilian control." https://t.co/RMTGMWMznP

name: NPR
text:
Despite the new stresses, women are drawing upon their inner strength to survive — and even thrive. "Women are responding in the ways that they often do: with an incredible display of resilience."

Here are the stories of 19 women around the world: https://t.co/4e6aWonrST

name: NPR
text:
Estée Lauder is reportedly paying $17,500 an hour to have astronauts take photos and videos of its skincare serum in space. NASA has set aside 90 hours of crew time for commercial and marketing activities like this.  
https://t.co/82Q7E6eZOm

name: NPR
text:
Graciela Iturbide has spent half a century capturing the beauty of her homeland — and calling for Mexico to reclaim its sense of pride and identity.

"There is no need to pursue the American dream," the photographer says. "We have our own here, too." https://t.co/jrrJOudKvQ
